You may (or may not) be surprised to know that almost 90% of my female clients HATE the way they look, especially in photos. Most of them hardly wear makeup and are shocked when they see themselves in full hair & makeup. We are our own worst critics, we know this. But like I tell everyone: No one, I repeat, NO ONE cares as much as you do. You are literally the only person who notices or cares about that wrinkle, or that little bit of extra weight, or whatever. So you’re stressing yourself out for who? Yourself?? Stop it lol This is what you look like and you look AMAZING! Own it, love it, flaunt it. And if worse comes to worse, that’s why we have photoshop 😂

Everytime someone says this, a photographer dies a little bit inside 😅 We spend a longggg, longggg time learning how to use all these little buttons, the science of lighting, colors, posing, etc. The camera is just a tool. If you know your craft, you can produce great images on a camera that doesn’t cost $4k+

Many would be surprised to know that most of my images were taken with a camera that costs less than $1k. I don’t have the most expensive lighting equipment; a lot of times I use natural light. Your belief that you need all of the top gadgets to do amazing work is false. Knowledge is your greatest asset - invest in that first. 💡

Hello to all the newbies here 👋🏻 

First off, welcome. Bienvenidos. 

I’m Jaquie, Jaquline, Jaq, Ja-qwelen (iykyk)… and I’ve been a full-time photographer for about 6 years in Miami, FL. Most of my followers know me from wayyy back in the modeling days of Maxim and such (shout out to my day ones). But now I’m on the other side of the lens, using my knowledge and experience from working in the industry for so so so many years, and bringing it to you. 

Here I give tips on all things photography, posing, feeling confident in your self & your selfie; as well as sprinkling in some humor and doodle content. So if that’s your vibe then stick around because it’s coming in hot 🔥

And if you’re feeling spicy & want to book a shoot with me, slide in my DMs, that’s where it goes down 😉 

Enjoy the show, kids!

3 Things People Do To Photographers That Slowly (but surely) Eat Away At Our Souls 👇🏻

1. Editing a photo we already edited. 
I get it, you want to be more involved… but don’t. Respectfully. You wouldn’t go to a fine dining restaurant and ask for A1 sauce with the Japanese Waygu Filet (I hope not). Let the artist be an artist, and you just enjoy. Now, let’s say you don’t like the edits. Politely let your photographer know and then go from there. Maybe they re-edit them, maybe they allow you to edit them. Just as long as both parties agree 👍🏻 

2. Not tagging your photographer 
I get it, you’re looking for the perfect caption. But please, don’t leave us out of it. It only takes a second and it helps us out A LOT. They helped you look your best, now help them make others look great too by doing this simple thing. 

3. Impatience 
If I told you the photos will take up to 14 business days, don’t text me the next day asking “how those photos going?” 😀 Because they’re still going. For up to 14 business days. And they’ll see you then. 

Glad we had this talk 😅

Just a little silly humor since this topic in my reel the other day caused quite the controversy 😅🤪🤭 

To tag or not to tag? That is the question.

For photographers, I think that’s entirely up to you whether you care if your clients tag you or not. For a lot of us, being tagged in our work is the core of our referral business. It’s one of those service industries where we rely on word of mouth (or caption). 

Personally, I don’t make my clients tag me in the photos, most of them are just good people who understand that is the courtesy you give to someone in our industry. And to them, I thank you 🙏🏻🥰

What do you think? 💭

👉🏼 Instantly look more photogenic with this hack! 

If you’re one of those people that will face forward or to the side when the camera is on you, remember this: You are a 3D object being turned into a 2D image. So the more dynamic you can make your pose, the better. Turning 45 degrees will give you more depth and dimension - which means more flattering!! This applies to men AND women. Try it out, you’ll look great 😘

“Can you hook me up?” 🙄😅

I get it… most people think photographers just push a button so why are we charging so much?!

Let’s see… thousands of $$ in equipment, years learning how to use that equipment, studying light and angles, the cost of running a business, not to mention the work done before AND after the shoot (which is where most of our time is spent)… But you’re also paying for our style, expertise, and the experience. If that doesn’t matter to you then go ahead and download that AI photo generating app. Like they say… you get what you pay for 🤭

And if you were wondering… yes, it shows!
